runs.comm: 150 km/h Tait angles into McCullum's pads and he clips it to long leg for a couple. Quick outfield.
153 km/h bouncer from Tait and McCullum is easily out of the way as he ducks
153 km/h good channel from Tait and McCullum pushes away from his body and misses

This one is quick again and McCullum pushes away from his body and it takes the outside edge and Haddin takes a remarkable catch diving full stretch to his right, snaring the ball in one hand. What a start!
153 km/h bouncer again from Tait to welcome Guptill to the crease and he ducks underneath
150 km/h good channel from Tait and Guptill allows it through to the keeper
147 km/h good start from Nannes as he bends his back and Ingram punches off the back foot to third man
147 kph angled down the leg side and not called wide. It may have taken he pad on the way through.
147 kph, good line and length, shouldered arms through to the keeper
149 kph, a touch fuller this time and Guptill tries to play a square drive but misses
147 kph, good length but too wide from Nannes and Guptill drives on the up through extra cover
149 kph, good channel from Nannes and allowed through to the keeper
150 kph, back of a length and Ingram drives off the back foot from the toes of the bat to cover point
149 kph, angled into his pads and Ingram whips it straight to square leg and Christian whips it to the bowlers end. Sharp from Christian.
153 kph, quick and short and Ingram is stringly in behind it and defending
155 kph, this one is short and rapid! Ingram goes inside the line comfortably, well played.
150 kph, another bouncer from Tait angled down leg and Ingram ducks underneath
153 kph, good channel and Ingram swings it off the outside edge to third man
150 kph, offers some width and Ingram back foot drives to point off the outside edge
150 kph, short and quick from Nannes as Ingram attempts to pull but misses and Haddin does well to get a glove on it
148 kph, back of a length and Guptill defends with soft hands behind the wicket
150 kph, back of a length played to backward point
148 kph, full on middle and leg and Guptill whips it through mid wicket for four
151 kph, good length angled across Guptill and he plays and misses
143 kph, great start from Johnson as he bowls back of a length and Ingram plays all around it trying to work it through the leg side and it takes out middle stump
146 kph, full and wide and Taylor looks to play a square drive but misses
149 kph, good length from Johnson and Taylor hangs the bat out to dry. Almost looks as if he didn't pick that one up.
149 kph, shorter from Johnson angled into Taylor's ribs and he works it fine off his glove for four. Haddin was close to catching that as he stuck out his left mit.
148 kph, good length and Taylor goes back and works it to mid wicket for a single
150 kph, Guptill plays it to point and there's a slight mix up as Clarke hits the stumps at the strikers end and Guptill is home safe
Taylor pushes to point and set off for the run, Guptill makes a late 'no' call and Clarke trhows at the strikers end but misses. Taylor was long gone!
back of a length and Taylor works it into the leg side and they take a sharp single
too short and Guptill is onto it quickly and pulls over mid wicket for four. Good stroke
fuller on leg stump and Guptill pushes nicely to mid on
short again and it hurries Guptill on the pull, taking the splice of the bat but it's once bounce four on these short boundaries
short and wide and he back cuts to third man where Tait bobbles it and they have enough time for an easy two
full on off stump and driven to deep point
good length from Johnson, a fraction straight and Guptill is back and defending with soft hands into the off side and they take a quick single
short and pulled from high on the bat forwrad of square for a couple to the sweeper on the leg side

Taylor walks across to the off side and looks to heave it over mid wicket but he misses and it takes him on his back foot outside the line of off stump and he's given out LBW. The hosts certainly didn't need that and Australia are rampant!
waist high full toss and Franklin works it to deep square leg
good length as Guptill tries to play to third man but misses. Well bowled
full and driven to long off
full and Guptill moves back and cuts to short third man
uses his feet and drives to the off side sweeper
good length from SMith and Franklin pushes back to the bowler
wrong'un from Smith and Franklin plays back down the pitch
shorter this time and Franklin pushes to long on
chipped over extra cover for a couple
played to long on
played nicely to the point boundary
played back to the bowler
yorker squeezed to mid wicket for a single
driven to long on
driven aerially to long off
played to mid wicket where Clarke fields well to save a run
uses his feet and chips to long on
played back to the bowler
chipped over the bowler, hit rather well and Hussey dives in the deep to save four
lapped fine for a couple
good length played to backward point
droppedgood length and Guptill pulls off the top edge. Haddin moves well towards square leg and puts it down!
played to deep square leg for a single
worked into the off side for a sharp single
short and Guptill pulls into mid wicket where Watson moves back from mid wicket and takes the catch half-way between the boundary and the 30m circle
angled into the pads and played to mid wicket off the pad
mistimes the cut to the off side.
moves forward and drives to the sweeper cover for a single.
fuller and driven down the ground to long on.
short ball and pulled well to deep backward square leg and picks up a single, fielded by Johnson.
not short for the pull, he goes for it and gets beaten, goes over the stumps to the keeper.
hit in the air down the ground and one bounce to the fielder at long on, single taken.
full and worked off the inside edge to the leg side sweeper
full and whipped off leg stump to fine leg
Dropped smashed straight back to the bowler, Christian throws a hand at it and they take one
gives himself room and square drives on one knee over cover. Super shot!
good length and pulled off the inside edge to fine leg
half volley on leg stump and Franklin helps it on its way over square leg for half a dozen
DROPPED slower ball which he tries to hit over the top but he hits it straight to Clarke who puts it down
attempts to drive, it takes the inside edge and falls into the off side
short ball and Franklin goes underneath
back of a length and driven neatly to long on
steps across to off stump and tries to heave it over the leg side but gets an edge into the off side
short and Franklin sees it early and pulls over square leg for a maximum
length ball and Hopkins upper cuts somehow over third man for six. He didn't really have the length to do that but the pace of Tait and it flies
full and hit to cover where Clarke misfields
back of a length and pushed to backward point
back of a length and guided off the outside edge for four. Super shot. Didn't seem to have the room but well played in the end.
good length but worled off the hip to the leg side sweeper
yorker but well down leg and Hopkins somehow gets the willow on it and it flies fine past Haddin for four
crunched down the ground in the air towards long on and Smith dives full stretch to get a hand to it and stop the boundary
slower ball and it's too wide but Franklin doesn't make him pay, cutting straight to point
fullish on middle and Franklin whips it behind square for four off the inside edge
good length and he drives back to Watson
full and crunched to long off
advances down the pitch and attempts to play over cover but takes the outside edge through to Haddin
back of a length and timed nicely back at Johnson who parries it to cover
short and wide and Franklin tries to cut but misses
half volley and Franklin hits it straight back over the bowler's head for a couple to long on
bouncer from Johnson and Franklin ducks underneath thinking it may well be a wide but not to be
fullish angled into leg and Franklin tries to whip it over the leg side but it takes him on the back leg
full and angled down the leg side, only just misses the leg stump
full and worked into mid wicket for an easy single
short and angled at the body and Oram pulls to mid wicket where Watson dives full stretch to his right and pulls of a superb one handed grab!
short and cut off the outside edge to third man
driven to mid off who is inside the circle
another bouncer and Franklin ducks underneath
half volley driven to mid off. This is turning out to be a great over from the former ski instructor
good length from Nannes, McCullum tries to pull, it takes him high on the bat and it loops to Hussey at mid on
full and wide and Franklin doesn't show any footwork to get closer to the ball and he misses well outside off just inside the wide line
yorker squeezed out to point where Clarke misfields and they take one
good length beats Vettori for pace and it goes over the top of middle stump and Haddin can't glove it cleanly
full delivery and Franklin drives down the ground in the air, he mistimes it and Smith dives forward to his left at mid off to take a good catch
steps away to the off side and actually gives himself too much room missing the ball it it goes just past the off stump
yorker played to the squarer of two third man fielders
steps away to leg this time and swats it to long on
slower ball and Tuffey plays far too early, it bounces just over middle stump and Haddin cannot clean up behind the stumps
good length and Vettori tries to swing it over the leg side but mistimes it to long off

Tuffey swings hard again and misses, Vettori calls him through for a bye, Haddin rolls to collect the ball as it bounces in front of him and he throws down the stumps in the same motion. Superb work from the keeper!
mistimed drive to long on
Tuffey moves across to outside off stump and it takes him on the thigh pad and Haddin collects it and half-appeals and umpire Baxter gives it out! Unlucky for Tuffey there
